  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Electrical Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead the electrical and instrument preliminary and detailed design processes to deliver accurate costing, procurement plans, and execution strategies for M&E projects</li><li>Perform engineering design tasks including load calculation, single line diagram (SLD) design, cable scheduling, cable routing, and instrument hookup to ensure compliance with project requirements</li><li>Develop and manage the bill of materials (BOM), project budget, and schedule to align with project goals and timelines</li><li>Monitor and update project schedules to track progress and mitigate delays</li><li>Oversee installation, testing, and commissioning activities on-site to ensure quality and safety standards are met</li><li>Manage and coordinate a team of electricians or subcontractors to execute installation tasks efficiently</li><li>Supervise procurement, storage, and usage of materials at the site to optimize resource allocation and minimize waste</li><li>Lead the clearance of punch lists by resolving outstanding issues to achieve project completion</li><li>Prepare and finalize as-built drawings to document the completed installation accurately</li><li>Compile and submit project documentation for client handover, ensuring completeness and compliance</li><li>Perform other ad-hoc duties as required to support project success</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor's Degree in Electrical and Electronic Engineering (EEE) or Electrical & Instrumentation (E&I)</li><li>Proficiency with AutoCAD software to produce detailed engineering drawing</li><li>Minimum 3 years of experience in M&E construction field demonstrating practical application of electrical design and project execution</li><li>Strong communication skills to collaborate effectively with team members and stakeholders</li><li>Ability to work independently while contributing as a collaborative team player</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
